        <name>22.3.1.4 Final key point</name>
        <questiontext>&lt;div class="HELM_keypoint"&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;Key Point&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An \(n\times n\) matrix with repeated eigenvalues can be diagonalized provided we can obtain \(n\) linearly independent eigenvectors for it. This will be the case if, for each repeated eigenvalue \(\lambda_i\), of multiplicity \(m_i&amp;gt;1\), we can obtain \(m_i\) linearly independent eigenvectors.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;</questiontext>
